*The Gini Coefficient measures the dispersion of income within a particular area. The closer a Gini coefficient is to 0, the more equitably distributed income is across a County's population. Gini coefficients closer to 1 signify greater income inequality.                                        Source: US Census Bureau, American Community Survey, 5 Year Estimates, 2006-2010, Table B19083
